    "comment": "Rationale: Fig.3: \"Reduced AMPAR-mediated glutamatergic synaptic transmission with aberrant dendritic spine morphology in PSD-Zip70KO mice\"\n\nFig.4: \"Decrease in mature spine synapses and aberrant activation of Rap2 in PSD-Zip70KO neurons\"\n\nFig.6: \"PSD-Zip70 modulates Rap2 activity via SPAR- and PDZ-GEF1\"\n\nFig.7: \"PSD-Zip70 regulates spine morphology via modulation of the Rap2 activity\"\n- \"In contrast, depleting all of the Rap2 subtypes (Rap2a, b, and c) or both PDZ-GEF1 and PDZ-GEF2 could recover the spine-morphology defects of PSD-Zip70KO neurons (Fig. 7d-f).\". Experimental description: - \"Here we generated PSD-Zip70 knock-out (PSD-Zip70KO) mice, ...\"\n- \"Cultured neurons were prepared from mouse embryonic brain on embryonic day 16.5 \"\n- \"The coding regions of mouse PSD-Zip70, Rap2, and rat SPAR were amplified by PCR and subcloned into the highly efficient mammalian expression plasmid pCAGGS. \"",
